<item>
            <title>[BEAM-6666] subprocess.Popen hangs after use of gRPC channel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-6666</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;subprocess.Popen randomly hangs after use of gRPC channel. This makes cross-language wordcount test fail&#160;because&#160;the test uses Popen to launch Dockerized Flink job server in `PortableRunner.run_pipeline` after use of gRPC channel for the expansion service in `ExternalTransform.expand`. Few symptoms are listed below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hanging at `docker_path = check_output(&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;#39;which&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;docker&amp;#39;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;).strip()`&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hanging at `self.docker_process = Popen(cmd)`&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Crashing with `assertion failed: pthread_mutex_lock(mu) == 0` message&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
